title = Important News Regarding Your Profile
heading = Changes to your { -brand-short-name } profile

changed-title = What changed?
changed-desc-profiles = If you are seeing this page, you are most likely one of the users who lost access to your existing Waterfox data after upgrading to Waterfox G3 recently. This installation of { -brand-short-name } has a new profile, but it is meant as a way for you to switch back to your preferred profile. A profile is the set of files where saved information such as bookmarks, passwords, and user preferences is stored.
changed-desc-dedicated = In order to make it easier and safer to switch between installations of  Waterfox Classic and Waterfox G3, this installation now has a dedicated profile. It does not automatically share your saved information with other installations.

lost = <b>You have not lost any personal data or customizations.</b> If you’ve already saved information to  on this computer, it is still available in another installation.

options-title = What are my options?
options-do-nothing = If you do nothing, you will start off with a new empty profile, again.
options-do-something = Head to <a href="about:profiles">about:profiles</a> and select your old profile as DEFAULT. After this is done, you can restart Waterfox and your profile data will be there!
options-use-sync = If you would like all of your profile data to be the same on all installations of Waterfox, you can use a { -fxaccount-brand-name } to keep them in sync.

